      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\"What's a puny fluid tank got when they're up against a $(bold)DYNAMIC TANK$().\" $(p)The Dynamic Tank is a multiblock structure that can hold both gas and fluid, albeit only one type of gas/fluid at once. The total capacity is defined by the size of your multiblock. $(p)Size limit: 18x18x18"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "$(bold)Blocks required:$()$(li)Dyanmic Tank $(li)Dynamic Valve $(li)Structural Glass"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "title": "Construction Notes",
        "text": "Construction Notes:$()$(li)The tank's length, width, and height can be any number within the size limit - e.g. 3x4x5.$(li)Total capcity is the volume of the multiblock (including base, walls, roof and frames) times 64,000mB."
      },
